gardner@convex.com (Steve Gardner) writes:

: >Actually, the speed of light is about 300 meters per microsecond.
: 	Oh, what's a couple of orders of magnitude anyway?

The difference between being able to mount an antenna on your car, and
having to have it guyed up and equipt with aircraft warning lights.

: 	Regardless, the problem still exists for reasonable distances 
: 	doesn't it?  How do you get around the  problem of the spatial 
: 	dependence of the synchronization (in the case of using a
: 	TV signal)? 

As long as you are using the same source for the sync signal, there is
no problem. All you need to know is the propogation time to the various
slave units.

